attributes.title: Doki Doki Literature Club - GAME CLUB #1
attributes.caption: Let's kick this off in the weirdest, most disturbing way possible! In our first episode, The crew plays Doki Doki Literature Club and compares game-inflicted emotional scars.
attributes.description:
Starting off with a weird note, we play Doki Doki Literature Club and compare our emotional scars afterwards. 
NOTE: This game contains disturbing content with themes of depression, suicide, self harm, obsession, and mental illness. Skip this one if you're sensitive.

attributes.title: Stardust - Movie Club #1
attributes.caption: Join us for our first movie club featuring Stardust! Sky pirates, fallen stars, sexy evil witches, young Henry Cavill with his actual accent, baby Daredevil, and Robert DeNiro in drag are just a few of the many brilliant things you can expect from the fil
attributes.description: We're not sleeping on this 2007 adaptation of the Neil Gaiman book! Join us for our first movie club featuring Stardust! Sky pirates, fallen stars, sexy evil witches, young Henry Cavill with his actual accent, baby Daredevil, and Robert DeNiro in drag are just a few of the many brilliant things you can expect from the film.

attributes.title: The Lies of Locke Lamora - Book Club #1
attributes.caption: This week we read The Lies of Locke Lamora by Scott Lynch, a heist caper starring a cast of lovable villains set against the backdrop of a compelling fantasy world
attributes.description:
This week we read The Lies of Locke Lamora by Scott Lynch, a slick heist caper starring an incredible cast of lovable villains set against the backdrop of a grounded imaginary world in the vein of George R.R. Martin or Joe Abercrombie, but a dash of humor reminiscent of Terry Pratchett. YOU SHOULD READ THIS BOOK!
NEXT WEEK: Mansions of Madness (Tabletop Club)
COMING UP: Little Nightmares (Game Club), Spirited Away (Movie Club), Neverwhere (Book Club)
